                        <i>Knowing God</i>, by J.I. Packer
                    </a>
                </pTitle>
                <br />
                <span class="more">
                    Consider this book by the late J.I. Packer as a systematic theology whereby he formulates an orderly presentation of the God
                    of the Bible. Here you will discover the great difference between knowing about God and possessing true knowledge of him. I
                    would consider this Packer’s greatest contribution to his spiritual legacy. If, as Tozer says, the most important thing about
                    you is how you perceive God, then this book is a must read.
                </span>
            </p>
